definition:
A man living at the time of the Patriarchs, first mentioned at Gen.5.32; 
 son of: Noah (H5146); 
 brother of: Shem (H8035) and Japheth (H3315); 
 father of: Canaan (H3667), Cush (H3568), Egypt (H4714) and Put (H6316)
 § Ham = "hot"
1) 2nd son of Noah, father of Canaan and of various peoples which were inhabitants of southern lands
2) in late usage, a collective name for Egyptians
